HEADWORD: Deculassment
<hw>Dec`u*lass"ment</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</mhw> <fld>(Ordnance)</fld> <def>An accidental blowing
off of, or other serious damage to, the breechblock of a gun; also, a
removal of the breechblock for the purpose of disabling the
gun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

